com.nttdocomo.ui
Class PhoneSystem

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.nttdocomo.ui.PhoneSystem
public class PhoneSystem
extends java.lang.Object

This defines the mobile phone device. The phone system class is a class that provides methods for accessing the native resources of the platform.

Method Detail

setAttribute

public static final void setAttribute(int attr,
                                      int value)
This controls native resources. When resource control is limited by UE settings, the restrictions are observed. When a resource type that does not exist has been designated, it is ignored and nothing generated.

Parameters:
attr - Designates the type of native resource attribute.
value - Designates the attribute to be set for native resources.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Generated when an illegal attribute value is designated for the argument value for valid resources designated by argument attr.
